reviews.text: Great place to live but not the friendliest community
So far so good for a regional market.
Better quality shopping than expected at the wet market. Although small, this market has everything you need to get by. It's really quite impressive. There are others stores at this mall.

Under LINK company, we can expected that the price would not cheap and restaurants choices are limit (monopoly and globalization), people prefer walk 15 mins to go to the another market to buy fish and vegetables. Since rent is high for the shops, most of the shops in the markets were closed down already.

This estate just bring Hung Shui Kiu a lot of uncivilized, bad educated new immigrants. No contribution to the community. Tax payers pay them a lot for the housing! The shops and restaurants in this area are all big chain store companies. Food is expensive and not fresh. I really can't think of what is good there. I will never go there unless I get off from the bus terminus.
非常美麗既公屋苑，設施齊全，得舒服既環境
新移民佔大部分嘅香港民居
我們的國家公園管理處將於本月底止全年業績將錄得綜合報導，我的心情是否受到影響，我的心情是否受到影響。
